transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra, how can I help you?

Speaker 2: Well, I'd like to check on my prescription.

Speaker 1: I believe it's on automatic refill.

Speaker 2: I'd like to check for how long and how often I'm getting them

Speaker 1: because they're kind of piling them up.

Speaker 2: I'm not using them that fast.

Speaker 1: Okay, no problem, Dennis, I can help you out.

Speaker 2: Can you just confirm your date of birth?

Speaker 1: 6-11-54.

Speaker 2: Thank you so much, I see you're a VIP status customer.

Speaker 1: Oh, okay, the doctor put you on refills on a monthly basis,

Speaker 2: which you do not have to have.

Speaker 1: You can change that to every two months, every three months.

Speaker 2: A lot of people just like to go ahead

Speaker 1: and put a six-month hold on it.

Speaker 2: That way it keeps you locked in at your rate

Speaker 1: and keeps your prescription active

Speaker 2: and just allows you to call in whenever you need a refill.

Speaker 1: I could pause that for you until July 31st, 2026.

Speaker 2: Will there be any kind of notification come July?

Speaker 1: You just have to put a reminder in your phone.

Speaker 2: Six months, I think that's probably a little too long.

Speaker 1: What am I getting, 10 a month?

Speaker 2: Yes, 10 a month.

Speaker 1: And then what were my options?

Speaker 2: You could do it in monthly increments,

Speaker 1: like every two months, every three months,

Speaker 2: every four months, every five months, up to six months.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Let's try every, if I go every three months

Speaker 1: and I need some, can I just call and get it refilled?

Speaker 2: Exactly, yeah, you can just call in

Speaker 1: whenever you need a refill.

Speaker 2: Okay, let's go every three months then.

Speaker 1: Okay, give me one second and I'll tell you your next date.

Speaker 2: It'll still just be the same amount, right, the 10?

Speaker 1: Yes, yes, the 10.

Speaker 2: Okay, so your next refill would go out to you

Speaker 1: on April 20th.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Yes, if you need a refill before then,

Speaker 2: give us a call, if not, or if you don't need one by then,

Speaker 1: you know, you can call us and you can pause it further.

Speaker 2: Okay, thank you.

Speaker 1: Yeah, not a problem, Dennis.

Speaker 2: Have a great day.

Speaker 1: You too, bye-bye.

Speaker 2: Bye.
